"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106222","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-10","<p>The Government takes the enforcement of the National Minimum Wage very seriously. Her Majesty’s Revenue and Customs (HMRC) review every complaint that is referred to them by the Pay and Work Rights Helpline. In addition, HMRC undertake targeted enforcement on employers across the United Kingdom who are more likely to be not paying National Minimum Wage.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC also undertake joint working with the police, Home Office and local authorities across the country in cases that may involve slavery and servitude, but do not keep statistics relating to any trafficking offences which may be taken forward by the relevant authorities.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-11-10T17:50:00.3755973Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106222/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106222/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106222/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-04","Human Trafficking","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many cases of human trafficking were uncovered by HM Revenue and Customs as part of its minimum wage enforcement activity in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013 and (e) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","213233"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106223","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-11","<p>I refer the hon. member to the answer [the Chancellor of the Exchequer] gave her on 2 September 2014, Official Report, column 221W</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-11-11T16:40:06.436196Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106223/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106223/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-04","Carbon Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 2 September 2014 to Question 207058, if he will discuss with (a) the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change and (b) the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills the implications for his policies on financial stability of the statements given to the World Bank seminar on integrated reporting on 10 October 2014 by the Governor of the Bank of England on unburnable carbon and market failures; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","213226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106224","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-07","<p>Since 2011, the Government has abolished the previous government’s fuel duty escalator, cut fuel duty by 1 pence per litre in March 2011 and scrapped four planned increases over the parliament. As a result of this Government’s actions, average pump prices are currently 16 pence per litre lower than they would have been under the previous Government’s fuel duty plans, and will be nearly 20 pence per litre lower by the end of the parliament.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2014-11-07T14:52:51.3347209Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106224/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106224/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106224/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-04","Fuels: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what effect changes to fuel duty have had on the price of petrol in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","213242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106225","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-19","<p>On 7 September the Government announced the government would extend the freeze on rail fares so that no regulated rail fares will increase by more than inflation.</p><p> </p><p>The Chancellor also announced that for 2015, train companies will no longer have the flexibility to increase some fares by 2% above the cap.</p><p> </p><p>As set out in the press release these measures will cost £100m by 2015/16.</p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-11-19T13:48:44.477Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106225/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106225/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106225/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-04","Railways: Fares","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the cost to the Exchequer of increasing regulated rail fares by RPI in 2015.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","213271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106226","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-12","<p>The Government is committed to tackling tax fraud and avoidance and has re-invested almost £1 billion in HMRC to strengthen the response to criminal attacks on the tax system, tax avoidance, and unpaid tax debt.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC’s response to non-compliance is tailored to the seriousness of the offence. HMRC is actively responding to the risks in the sector, and working with the National Crime Agency to develop and deliver a comprehensive multi-agency waste sector campaign.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Visits to landfill sites are one part of HMRC’s response to landfill tax compliance.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In addition to these visits and audit checks, HMRC has launched a cross-tax waste sector pilot exercise which is currently under way, where cases are being worked across all taxes, rather than just landfill tax. HMRC is also working collaboratively with other agencies to tackle non-compliance and develop a joined up multi-agency strategy, capitalising on the full range of sanctions available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC adopts a risk-based approach to compliance activity to enable resources to be deployed flexibly to areas of highest risk and does not therefore allocate budgets to any particular tax regime</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC’s management information systems are unable to identify the number of complaints received specifically about the non-payment of landfill tax without incurring disproportionate costs.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel","213277 ; 213278 ; 213279 ; 213280 ; 213281 ; 213282 ; 213284","2014-11-12T11:52:52.1349556Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106226/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106226/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106226/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-04","Landfill Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask