"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106227","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-11","<p>The cost to print and post annual tax summaries sent to individual taxpayers is estimated to be around £5.3m.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-11-11T17:13:30.0754454Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106227/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106227/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106227/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-04","Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much was spent on collating, distributing and mailing the recently sent annual tax summary letter.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","213257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106228","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-10","<p>The Government has increased spending to prevent and tackle homelessness, making over £500 milion available to councils and the voluntary sector. Local authorities are required to provide advice and information to single homeless people who approach them.<br><br>We have launched an £8 million Help for Single Homeless Fund for local auhtorities which will improve council services for single people facing the prospect of homelessness by encouraging better partnership working between councils and other local partners.</p><p> </p><p>We are also helping single homeless people to find and sustain accomodation in the private rented sector through our £13 million funding to Crisis. By 2016 we expect the Crisis scheme to have helped 10,000 single homeless people.</p><p> </p><p>In addition No Second Night Out schemes and Streetlink have helped thousands of vulnerable people who have slept rough or were at risk of doing so to get the help they need.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-11-10T16:24:32.9432931Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106228/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106228/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/106228/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-04","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent assessment he has made of the support available to single homeless people.","false","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","213238"
